qas.question: What was Nasser's first title in the Liberation Rally?
What did Nasser and naguib ban in 1953?
What was Nasser alone in supporting?

answers.text: British withdrawal from the Suez Canal

context: In January 1953, Nasser overcame opposition from Naguib and banned <a1_0>all political parties<a1_0/>, creating a one-party system under the Liberation Rally, a loosely structured movement whose chief task was to organize pro-RCC rallies and lectures, with Nasser its <a0_0>secretary-general<a0_0/>. Despite the dissolution order, Nasser was the only RCC member who still favored holding <a2_0>parliamentary elections<a2_0/>, according to his fellow officer Abdel Latif Boghdadi. Although outvoted, he still advocated holding elections by 1956. In March 1953, Nasser led the Egyptian delegation negotiating a <a3_0>British withdrawal from the Suez Canal<a3_0/>.
